<br>
The proc on the GSot4W is really inconsequential, it's just added DPS for all intents and purposes.<br>
<br>
GSoT is not even in the same league of DPS, IMO, but usually holds aggro really well for me due to the stun proc.<br>
<br>
So how do you get GSoT aggro and GSot4W DPS?<br>
<br>
As Bippin said, try to get an augment for the GSot4W.  A Ykesha proc would be great, and Anger (2 or 3, I'd say) is great as well.  Something to keep in mind,  an augmented proc does not go off unless the weapon fails the first check for a proc.  So an Anger proc wouldn't check to fire unless you missed the roll on the chance to activate the primary proc.<br>
<br>
After all that dungeon grinding, just get the applicable 2-handed AA for some extra swings (Ferocity, Flurry, Punishing Blade) and you will start being a respectable damage melee, at least enough to make lots of Monks cry (and rightfully so).<br>
